1
00:00:05,481 --> 00:00:08,000
You!

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:08,878
And you!

3
00:00:11,723 --> 00:00:15,397
You are the student committee, but you are the ones who breached the rules.

4
00:00:16,235 --> 00:00:19,129
What are the rules for if you don’t keep them?

5
00:00:19,769 --> 00:00:22,296
You’re lucky no one caught you

6
00:00:23,599 --> 00:00:25,000
or all of us would be screwed.

7
00:00:26,127 --> 00:00:27,508
But Miss Al,

8
00:00:27,508 --> 00:00:30,209
we didn’t get caught, did we?

9
00:00:30,209 --> 00:00:31,177
Stop backtalking.

10
00:00:37,064 --> 00:00:38,422
Even though you didn’t get caught,

11
00:00:38,864 --> 00:00:42,790
I, as the student president, will punish you guys myself.

12
00:00:45,917 --> 00:00:51,701
Every one of you must clean the student committee room for the whole semester.

13
00:00:53,374 --> 00:00:55,741
Don’t even let me see PM2.5 dust in here.

14
00:00:56,896 --> 00:00:57,572
But…

15
00:00:57,572 --> 00:00:58,346
No ‘buts.’

16
00:00:59,281 --> 00:01:00,616
Unless you want toilet cleaning duty too.

17
00:01:01,792 --> 00:01:02,875
Do you want that?

18
00:01:08,174 --> 00:01:09,234
Hello.

19
00:01:09,234 --> 00:01:10,541
Good morning, seniors.

20
00:01:14,386 --> 00:01:15,096
Oh.

21
00:01:15,279 --> 00:01:17,923
I guess you guys are busy.

22
00:01:17,923 --> 00:01:19,298
I’ll leave you to it then. Goodbye.

23
00:01:19,665 --> 00:01:20,649
You too, Tinh.

24
00:01:21,566 --> 00:01:22,184
Come here.

25
00:01:26,174 --> 00:01:27,275
Hey, Alpha.

26
00:01:27,711 --> 00:01:29,716
Don’t punish him.

27
00:01:30,748 --> 00:01:33,240
We, seniors, should take responsibility.

28
00:01:36,075 --> 00:01:36,848
Fine.

29
00:01:37,421 --> 00:01:41,102
There will be no punishment for you because you’re younger.

30
00:01:41,361 --> 00:01:42,121
Really?

31
00:01:42,511 --> 00:01:43,155
But…

32
00:01:44,495 --> 00:01:47,492
you must be Mawin’s assistant for the whole semester.

33
00:01:48,134 --> 00:01:48,739
Huh?

34
00:02:02,407 --> 00:02:05,505
(Though I could get through last night without punishment,)

35
00:02:06,698 --> 00:02:10,000
(there’s still a big deal waiting for me today.)

36
00:02:11,452 --> 00:02:14,599
(I almost forgot that I have a basketball game with Blossom.)

37
00:02:30,001 --> 00:02:31,236
How’s your foot?

38
00:02:32,001 --> 00:02:33,202
Does it feel any better?

39
00:02:34,035 --> 00:02:34,739
Mhm.

40
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:35,860
It’s been better.

41
00:02:39,452 --> 00:02:40,354
Ongsa.

42
00:02:42,212 --> 00:02:44,426
Are you really competing with Blossom?

43
00:02:46,467 --> 00:02:47,269
Mhm.

44
00:02:47,980 --> 00:02:49,896
I must collect all the fees.

45
00:02:53,015 --> 00:02:54,961
How about I try to talk to her?

46
00:02:56,176 --> 00:02:57,075
It’s okay.

47
00:02:57,419 --> 00:02:58,735
I’ll handle it.

48
00:03:01,143 --> 00:03:02,872
But your foot hurts.

49
00:03:03,804 --> 00:03:05,529
You can’t play.

50
00:03:07,141 --> 00:03:10,104
(Why am I always the one who gets help from Sun?)

51
00:03:12,135 --> 00:03:13,176
Thank you, Sun,

52
00:03:13,956 --> 00:03:17,577
but this time I want to try it myself

53
00:03:18,311 --> 00:03:19,888
without any help.

54
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:23,883
Then do your best.

55
00:03:24,365 --> 00:03:25,645
I’ll be cheering for you.

56
00:03:26,815 --> 00:03:27,489
Mhm.

57
00:03:28,773 --> 00:03:34,095
(I hope Sun develops a more positive opinion toward you, Ongsa.)

58
00:03:44,847 --> 00:03:46,411
Ongsa, do your best.

59
00:03:46,411 --> 00:03:47,078
Fight hard, girl.

60
00:03:47,078 --> 00:03:48,298
Don’t back down.

61
00:03:50,725 --> 00:03:52,032
You can do it.

62
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:53,471
Ongsa!

63
00:03:53,471 --> 00:03:54,574
Ongsa, keep fighting.

64
00:03:59,600 --> 00:04:00,258
Ongsa, keep fighting.

65
00:04:00,258 --> 00:04:01,462
Ongsa, hang in there.

66
00:04:01,462 --> 00:04:02,502
Go, girl!

67
00:04:04,715 --> 00:04:06,715
- Ongsa, go!
- Ongsa, keep going.

68
00:04:06,715 --> 00:04:07,875
Ongsa, keep fighting.

69
00:04:07,875 --> 00:04:09,678
I’m giving you blessings…

70
00:04:09,678 --> 00:04:11,186
Ongsa, go, go.

71
00:04:13,067 --> 00:04:14,360
One point for Blue.

72
00:04:16,379 --> 00:04:17,989
Blossom, you did great.

73
00:04:20,426 --> 00:04:22,495
It’s okay, Ongsa. Try again.

74
00:04:22,839 --> 00:04:25,000
You can do it. Start over.

75
00:04:26,577 --> 00:04:27,774
Go, Ongsa.

76
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:30,645
Ongsa, keep fighting.

77
00:04:32,112 --> 00:04:33,684
Keep fighting, Ongsa.

78
00:04:34,750 --> 00:04:36,000
Hey!

79
00:04:43,770 --> 00:04:45,587
Two points for Blue.

80
00:04:46,569 --> 00:04:47,858
Ongsa, are you hurt?

81
00:04:47,987 --> 00:04:49,987
Ongsa, keep going. You can do it.

82
00:04:50,886 --> 00:04:52,336
Ongsa, fight her.

83
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:59,040
Ongsa, keep fighting.

84
00:04:59,723 --> 00:05:00,762
You can do it.

85
00:05:00,762 --> 00:05:01,723
Keep going.

86
00:05:08,928 --> 00:05:10,286
Keep trying, Ongsa.

87
00:05:10,286 --> 00:05:11,265
You can do it.

88
00:05:12,704 --> 00:05:13,861
Hey!

89
00:05:13,953 --> 00:05:14,888
Hey, Blossom, are you okay?

90
00:05:14,888 --> 00:05:16,909
Ongsa, the ball.

91
00:05:16,909 --> 00:05:17,937
Get the ball.

92
00:05:17,937 --> 00:05:18,806
Ongsa, hurry up.

93
00:05:20,721 --> 00:05:21,649
Shoot.

94
00:05:22,721 --> 00:05:24,045
Ongsa, you can do it.

95
00:05:24,045 --> 00:05:25,557
Go, Ongsa.

96
00:05:26,326 --> 00:05:27,111
Shoot it.

97
00:05:27,111 --> 00:05:27,833
Ongsa, shoot.

98
00:05:27,833 --> 00:05:28,704
Ongsa, go for it.

99
00:05:28,704 --> 00:05:29,842
You can do it.

100
00:05:29,842 --> 00:05:31,170
Fight!

101
00:05:31,408 --> 00:05:33,408
Whoo-hoo.

102
00:05:43,427 --> 00:05:44,377
The game ended.

103
00:05:44,377 --> 00:05:47,440
Blue wins by 8-0.

104
00:05:50,735 --> 00:05:55,280
(In the end, you’re still a loser as always, Ongsa.)

105
00:06:07,357 --> 00:06:07,857
Here.

106
00:06:07,857 --> 00:06:08,605
The fee.

107
00:06:15,210 --> 00:06:16,489
But I lost.

108
00:06:17,509 --> 00:06:20,724
How could an amateur beat a member of the school team, right?

109
00:06:21,134 --> 00:06:22,413
Your leg also hurts.

110
00:06:23,514 --> 00:06:25,729
I was impressed you could steal the ball from me at all.

111
00:06:27,105 --> 00:06:30,164
For such a timid person, you’re one hell of a fighter.

112
00:06:30,714 --> 00:06:31,271
Here.

113
00:06:32,303 --> 00:06:33,225
Thank you.

114
00:06:41,596 --> 00:06:44,445
(At least you did it, Ongsa.)

115
00:06:45,505 --> 00:06:47,505
(You have collected all the money.)

116
00:06:58,865 --> 00:06:59,747
Hello, Aylin.

117
00:07:01,513 --> 00:07:02,631
Can you hear me?

118
00:07:05,102 --> 00:07:06,134
I guess you can.

119
00:07:06,707 --> 00:07:08,501
I’m done with the basketball game.

120
00:07:08,852 --> 00:07:10,485
Waiting for you in front of Building 3 as always.

121
00:07:13,634 --> 00:07:14,640
Do you hear me?

122
00:07:18,263 --> 00:07:19,211
You do.

123
00:07:19,716 --> 00:07:20,506
See you.

124
00:07:28,081 --> 00:07:29,069
Ongsa.

125
00:07:34,963 --> 00:07:38,727
See? I told you you could do it.

126
00:07:40,001 --> 00:07:41,474
But I lost.

127
00:07:42,420 --> 00:07:46,240
I could collect all the money because Blossom was nice enough.

128
00:07:46,852 --> 00:07:49,655
But it’s because you didn’t give up.

129
00:07:50,857 --> 00:07:53,843
What you did today was so cool.

130
00:07:55,924 --> 00:07:56,867
(Cool?)

131
00:07:57,096 --> 00:07:59,346
(Did she just say I was cool?)

132
00:08:01,210 --> 00:08:02,840
Why are you making that face?

133
00:08:04,730 --> 00:08:06,248
Don’t you believe me?

134
00:08:07,264 --> 00:08:08,599
Um…

135
00:08:09,592 --> 00:08:13,266
No one has ever said I was cool before.

136
00:08:14,573 --> 00:08:15,314
Really?

137
00:08:26,874 --> 00:08:29,356
Then listen to me carefully.

138
00:08:31,243 --> 00:08:35,146
What you did today was so damn cool.

139
00:08:43,268 --> 00:08:52,653
So cool that you’d attract all the girls in our school if you were a guy.

140
00:08:54,503 --> 00:08:55,531
(Right. I forgot.)

141
00:08:57,022 --> 00:08:58,934
(You’re not a guy, Ongsa.)

142
00:09:05,418 --> 00:09:07,418
You’re exaggerating.

143
00:09:08,071 --> 00:09:09,147
It’s true.

144
00:09:09,445 --> 00:09:10,552
Not exaggerating.

145
00:09:11,681 --> 00:09:14,094
Ongsa, you’re the coolest.

146
00:09:17,093 --> 00:09:18,680
I’m headed home now.

147
00:09:19,719 --> 00:09:20,846
See you tomorrow.

148
00:09:21,419 --> 00:09:22,475
Get home safe.

149
00:09:25,001 --> 00:09:26,152
Bye-bye.

150
00:09:31,935 --> 00:09:33,069
Are you all right, human?

151
00:09:34,651 --> 00:09:35,907
It’s nothing.

152
00:09:37,172 --> 00:09:37,962
Is it about Sun?

153
00:09:37,962 --> 00:09:38,462
Hey!

154
00:09:41,008 --> 00:09:42,268
How did you know that?

155
00:09:44,301 --> 00:09:45,174
I took a wild guess.

156
00:09:46,435 --> 00:09:47,172
Aylin.

157
00:09:49,878 --> 00:09:51,603
Please don’t tell anyone about this.

158
00:09:52,229 --> 00:09:53,560
About human Ongsa liking human Sun?

159
00:09:53,560 --> 00:09:54,229
Hey!

160
00:09:59,722 --> 00:10:00,317
What?

161
00:10:00,867 --> 00:10:02,272
Ongsa, you like Sun?

162
00:10:02,455 --> 00:10:02,993
Hey!

163
00:10:19,464 --> 00:10:23,322
Our Astronomy Club will be holding Astrological Fortune Readings.

164
00:10:23,322 --> 00:10:27,026
You two must be the fortune tellers on the Club Fair day.

165
00:10:27,026 --> 00:10:28,439
Aylin and I?

166
00:10:28,679 --> 00:10:30,871
For our Astronomy Club,

167
00:10:31,215 --> 00:10:32,052
keep fighting.

168
00:10:32,052 --> 00:10:32,779
Fight.

169
00:10:32,779 --> 00:10:39,842
Borrowing power from the stars to foretell fortune requires you to sell the power of your own soul.

170
00:10:41,373 --> 00:10:43,579
Ongsa, Do you want my help with Sun?

171
00:10:44,093 --> 00:10:45,392
Sun, would you like your fortune told?

172
00:10:45,392 --> 00:10:46,320
I was born on Friday.

173
00:10:46,320 --> 00:10:47,863
Ongsa was born on Tuesday.

174
00:10:47,863 --> 00:10:51,043
That’s why I felt like we hit it off especially well.

175
00:10:51,043 --> 00:10:52,358
Our fortunes are compatible.

176
00:10:53,982 --> 00:10:57,037
Let’s say I like someone.

177
00:10:57,037 --> 00:11:00,122
How likely is it that the person will reciprocate my feelings?

178
00:11:02,745 --> 00:11:03,542
Very likely.

179
00:11:06,156 --> 00:11:08,460
That person must like you very much.
